I"9<p>Now rapidly moving away from both the sun and the eaarth, Comet Lovejoy (C/2020 F3) was only discovered a few months ago and turned out to be the brightest comet visible from the northern hemisphere in the past twenty years.</p>

<p>Finally we has a partially clear (although hazy) sky this past Sunday evening and I was able to take a few images before the comet set behind the trees to the northwest.</p>

